    bibo:volume "1351" ;
    dc:creator "Evenhuis, Neal L." ;
    dc:date "2006" ;
    dc:title "First record of the frog parasite genus Batrachomyia Krefft from New Guinea (Diptera: Chloropidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273600>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273598>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273599> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273600>
    dc:description "FIGURES 5 – 6. Batrachomyia last instar, ventral view. Detail of anterior portion of larva. 5. B. krausi, sp. nov., showing medial patches of microspicules on segments. 6. B. nigritarsis, showing medial row of small spinules on segments." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/273600/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273598>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 2. Batrachomyia, third (last) instar larval habitus, dorsal view. 1. B. krausi, sp. nov. 2. B. nigritarsis Skuse (Royal National Park, NSW; AMS specimen). Abbreviations; ar = anterior respiratory process; t = lateral tubercle; pr = posterior respiratory process." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/273598/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273599>
    dc:description "FIGURES 3 – 4. Batrachomyia last instar, dorsal view. Detail of anterior portion of larva. 3. B. krausi, sp. nov. 4. B. nigritarsis. Abbreviations. ar = anterior respiratory process; t = tubercle; dw = dorsal welts." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/273599/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

